HEADWORD: Coving
<hw>Cov"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Arch.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>A cove or series of coves, as the concaved surface
under the overhang of a projecting upper story.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>The splayed jambs of a flaring fireplace.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

